org.openbase.jul.extension.protobuf

Class MessageObservable<M extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openbase.jul.pattern.AbstractObservable<M>
      • org.openbase.jul.extension.protobuf.MessageObservable<M>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Shutdownable, Observable<M>

    public class MessageObservable<M extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends AbstractObservable<M>
    This class computes the hashCode to check if the observed value has changed invariant of its timestamp. Currently for efficiency reasons the timestamp of messages in repeated fields is still considered.
    Author:
    Tamino Huxohl

      • waitForValue

        public void waitForValue(long timeout,
                         TimeUnit timeUnit)
                  throws CouldNotPerformException,
                         InterruptedException
        Description copied from interface: Observable
        Method blocks until the observable is available. In case the given timeout is reached an TimeoutException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        timeout - is the timeout related to the given TimeUnit.
        timeUnit - is the unit of the timeout.
        Throws:
        CouldNotPerformException - is thrown with a TimeoutException cause if the given timeout is reached.
        InterruptedException - is thrown if the current thread was interrupted externally.
